country.name: Netherlands
country.overview: The Netherlands, a country in northwestern Europe, is known for a flat landscape of canals, tulip fields, windmills and cycling routes. Amsterdam, the capital, is home to the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum and the house where Jewish diarist Anne Frank hid during WWII. Canalside mansions and a trove of works from artists including Rembrandt and Vermeer remain from the city's 17th-century \"Golden Age.\"

geography.location_description: Western Europe, bordering the North Sea, between Belgium and Germany
geography.area_note: slightly less than twice the size of New Jersey
geography.climate: temperate; marine; cool summers and mild winters
geography.terrain: mostly coastal lowland and reclaimed land (polders); some hills in southeast
geography.notes: located at mouths of three major European rivers (Rhine, Maas or Meuse, and Schelde)
